race may be looming if developments are left unattended, and to provide policy options on how it-and it's devastating consequences-could be avoided. After identifying weaknesses in the international regime structures revolving around the Biological Weapons and Chemical Weapons Conventions, it provides policy proposals to deal with gaps and shortcomings in each prohibition regime individually, and then addresses the widening gap between them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Arms Control.2bisacsh1 aDando, Malcolm, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aNixdorff, Kathryn, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804786157zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804786157423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804786157.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles